{"title_page": "Daniel Reveles", "text_new": "{{notability|date=November 2019}}\n'''Daniel Reveles''' is an [[United States|American]] fiction writer who lives on the outskirts of [[Tecate]], [[Baja California]], [[Mexico]].  He was born in [[Los Angeles]] to Mexican parents, where he worked as a radio DJ and television writer, director, and producer for many years. In 1977 he retired to Tecate.\n\nReveles is known for his stories about Tecate, collected in ''Enchiladas, Rice and Beans'' (1994), ''Tequila, Lemon and Salt'' (2005), and ''Guacamole Dip'' (2008).  He received the 2004 Theodor S. Geisel Award from the [[San Diego Book Awards Association]] for ''Tequila, Lemon and Salt''.[https://web.archive.org/web/20080512092434/http://www.sdbookawards.org/geisel.php]\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.signonsandiego.com/uniontrib/20041031/news_m1a31reveles.html The torchbearer of Tecate] by  Arthur Salm, ''The San Diego Union-Tribune'', October 31, 2004.\n\n==External links==\n*{{worldcat id|lccn-no94-33343}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080716054640/http://www.danielreveles.com/ Reveles' website]\n*{{OL author}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Reveles, Daniel}}\n[[Category:Writers from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:American male writers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{US-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{notability|date=November 2019}}\n'''Daniel Reveles''' is an [[United States|American]] fiction writer who lives on the outskirts of [[Tecate]], [[Baja California]], [[Mexico]].  He was born in [[Los Angeles]] to Mexican parents, where he worked as a radio DJ and television writer, director, and producer for many years. In 1977 he retired to Tecate.\n\nReveles is known for his stories about Tecate, collected in ''Enchiladas, Rice and Beans'' (1994), ''Tequila, Lemon and Salt'' (2005), and ''Guacamole Dip'' (2008).  He received the 2004 Theodor S. Geisel Award from the [[San Diego Book Awards Association]] for ''Tequila, Lemon and Salt''.[https://web.archive.org/web/20080512092434/http://www.sdbookawards.org/geisel.php]\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.signonsandiego.com/uniontrib/20041031/news_m1a31reveles.html The torchbearer of Tecate] by  Arthur Salm, ''The San Diego Union-Tribune'', October 31, 2004.\n\n==External links==\n*{{worldcat id|lccn-no94-33343}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080716054640/http://www.danielreveles.com/ Reveles' website]\n*{{OL author}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Reveles, Daniel}}\n[[Category:Writers from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:American male writers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{US-writer-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daniel_Reveles"}
